# A mixed non-tilde generic hole (T string | int -> catAnyMixed, same shape as
# interpolation/url_hole_generic.txtar's generic component prop) inside an
# f`…@{…}…` literal at a top-level func return: holeStringExpr's catAnyMixed
# case (emit.go ~3502) would normally route the value through a hoisted
# rt.AttrString(...) conversion, which returns (string, error) — but a
# Go-expression position has no statement context to hoist that error into, so
# gsx rejects it with a positioned goexpr-literal-error rather than splicing
# invalid Go.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

func mk[T string | int](v T) string { return f`Hi @{v}` }

component Page(v string) {
	<div>{ mk(v) }</div>
}
-- invoke --
Page(PageProps{V: "a"})
-- diagnostics.golden --
3:52: @{ v } is a mixed type-parameter value (its runtime conversion can fail); a js`/css`/f` literal in Go-expression position has no error channel to propagate it through — handle the error in Go, or move the literal to an attribute position
-- render.golden --
